Package: BayesianId
Type: Package
Title: Regression analysis that actually answers your questions (using Bayesian model averaging).
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Paskewitz", "Samuel",
      email = "samuel.paskewitz@yale.edu",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: The main purpose of this package is to provide the data analyst with the posterior probabilities of hypotheses through Bayesian model averaging of nested regression model. The package provides pre-compiled Stan regression models for this purpose, which can be fit using either the Laplace approximation or Markov chain Monte Carlo sampling. You can also use regression models fit by maximum likelihood (e.g. "glm") with the BIC approximation.
